buildings seldom look as good as the renderings artists make of
them. But whose fault is that? The truth is that few people are
born with sharp eyes. When vision is not cultivated by memory,
shock and enthusiasm, the world can look remarkably dull. Eye
training class is now in session at the Museum of the City of New
York, where a trio of shows offers three startlingly different ways
of looking at the evolution of 20th-century New York. By Herbert
Muschamp.
</P>
