<HEADLINE>
USC'S DAVIS FACES SURGERY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC defensive tackle Ennis Davis suffered knee
ligament damage in the Sun Bowl and may not be fully recovered in
time for the Trojans' season-opener against Hawaii in September.
</P>
<P>
   Davis injured his left knee during USC's 28-19 loss to Texas
Christian University. Originally, Davis' injury was diagnosed as a
sprained knee but ligament damage was detected upon USC's return to
Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   Davis, who will have surgery either late this week or next week,
is expected to need at least nine months to rehabilitate. He was a
key performer for USC's defense this season and perhaps its
most-improved lineman.
</P>
<P>
   The Reseda High School graduate was an All-Pacific-10 Conference
first-team performer, with 47 tackles, including 13 for loss, and
three sacks. He also broke up four passes.
</P>
<P>
   Recruiting update: USC has received an oral commitment from
offensive lineman Lenny Vandermade of Mater Dei. Vandermade (6-3,
265 pounds) is the second offensive lineman from Orange County to
commit to the Trojans, joining Nate Steinbacher of Esperanza High
School.
</P>
<P>
   Big weekend: USC's recruiting resumes this weekend, with some of
the players scheduled to visit including offensive lineman Bryce
Bohlander of Salem (Ore.) McNary, defensive back Ricky Manning of
Fresno Edison, linebacker Omar Nazel of Oakland Skyline and
linebacker Lance Briggs of Sacramento Elk Grove.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
