<DOCNO> NYT19990108.0054 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-08 02:25 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A4331 &Cx1f; tth-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-SEAHAWKS-SPI &LR;      01-08 0757
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-SEAHAWKS-SPI </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HOLMGREN CHEWING ON SEAHAWKS JOB 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By CLARE FARNSWORTH  
 c.1999 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   KIRKLAND _ After meeting with Seahawks president Bob Whitsitt
for most of the day, Green Bay Packers coach Mike Holmgren left the
team's headquarters Thursday night to have dinner with owner Paul
Allen.
</P>
<P>
   Was it just food for thought? Or a meal to make a deal?
</P>
<P>
   Neither side was tipping its hand _ Whitsitt, or Holmgren and
his agent, Bob LaMonte.
</P>
<P>
   But when Dennis Erickson was fired last week, Whitsitt was asked
about Allen's involvement in the process of hiring a new coach.
</P>
<P>
   ``I would expect when we get down to the final meeting of our
choice, that Paul will be in the meeting,'' Whitsitt said. ``It is
important for the head coach to know who the owner is and for the
owner to know who the coach is, and to have that chemistry.
</P>
<P>
   ``Paul won't be involved in the process until we get to that
point.''
</P>
<P>
   Allen, who had been out of town, became involved Thursday night,
prompting speculation that if the team's owner agreed to the length
and financial terms of a contract and the parameters of Holmgren's
power as general manager and coach, a deal could be completed as
early as Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Before starting his whirlwind tour, which is supposed to include
weekend visits to the Baltimore Ravens and Philadelphia Eagles,
LaMonte said Holmgren's priorities in selecting a new team would be
strong ownership, complete control of the football operation and a
state-of-the-art stadium and practice facility.
</P>
<P>
   The biggest problem was expected to be determining just how much
power Holmgren would have in his dual role of GM and coach. But a
league source said Thursday night that a major sticking point with
Holmgren is accessibility to Allen, who attends most home games but
is rarely at the team's headquarters and has minimal contact with
management or players other than Whitsitt.
</P>
<P>
   That's why Thursday night's dinner with Allen was so vital to
Holmgren, who pushed for meetings with the owners in each of the
three cities he is scheduled to visit.
</P>
<P>
   Despite reports earlier in the day that Holmgren might delay his
trip to Baltimore, the Ravens are expecting Holmgren to keep his
appointment. The club has chartered a jet that is scheduled to fly
Holmgren, his wife, Kathy, and their youngest daughter, Gretchen,
to Baltimore at noon Friday.
</P>
<P>
   What Whitsitt said last week, and what happened Thursday night
when Allen hosted Holmgren for dinner at his Mercer Island estate,
were more revealing than anything that was said when Whitsitt and
Holmgren left the team's headquarters Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're having a good day. It's been productive,'' Whitsitt
said, facing a row of six TV cameras and three print photographers
and surrounded by a dozen newspaper reporters. ``Obviously, we
still have more conversations to continue with, which we will do
into the evening.''
</P>
<P>
   Holmgren declined to talk with reporters, but offered in a
statement: ``We have had a good day getting to know Bob, Randy
(Mueller, vice president of football operations) and the
organization and we will continue to talk. I've been impressed with
a number of things, including the design of the new stadium.''
</P>
<P>
   The Seahawks have been aggressively interested in Holmgren all
along. When the Packers were eliminated from the playoffs with
Sunday's loss to the 49ers, the Seahawks were the first team to
call to ask permission to speak with Holmgren _ at 7 a.m. Monday.
It was then, a league source said Thursday night, that the club
said it could offer a five-year, $21 million contract.
</P>
<P>
   Holmgren has one year left on his contract with the Packers but
was given a clause last February that provided a 21-day window that
allows him to accept a GM/coach position with another club.
</P>
<P>
   Holmgren was flown to Seattle from Green Bay on Allen's private
jet Wednesday and taken to a downtown hotel in a stretch limousine.
He meet with Whitsitt for more than two hours at the hotel Thursday
morning, before they met for five more hours at the team's
headquarters.
</P>
<P>
   During his visit to the team's complex, Holmgren talked with
Mueller, toured the facility and saw models of the new stadium that
is scheduled to open for the 2002 season.
</P>
<P>
   While Holmgren was busy with that, his wife and daughter toured
the campus at Seattle Pacific University. A senior in high school,
Gretchen reportedly called the school last week to inquire about
enrolling next fall.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
