<SLUG> BC-BANANAS-BOX-$ADV10-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    BANANA BATTLE MAY YIELD HIGH PRICES ON OTHER GOODS
 &HT;    With LATAM-BANANAS-$ADV10.
 &HT;    Moving in the both (i) International and (f) Financial
categories.
 &HT;    For Use Sun., Jan. 10 And Thereafter.
 &HT;    By SHELLEY EMLING 
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service 
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI _ The imposition of increased tariffs as a result of a
banana trade dispute between the United States and European Union
would affect a number of European imports. The following consumer
goods are expected to increase in price if a proposed U.S. tariff
increase holds:
</P>
<P>
   Pecorino cheese
</P>
<P>
   Sweet biscuits; waffles and wafers
</P>
<P>
   Bath preparations, other than bath salts
</P>
<P>
   Handbags
</P>
<P>
   Some candles
</P>
<P>
   Nonadhesive plates, sheets, film, foil
</P>
<P>
   Folding cartons, boxes and cases of noncorrugated paper
</P>
<P>
   Sweaters, and similar articles made of cashmere
</P>
<P>
   Some bed linens
</P>
<P>
   Lead-acid storage batteries
</P>
<P>
   Electrothermic coffee or tea makers
</P>
<P>
   Chandeliers
</P>
<P>
   Printed cards (except postcards) bearing personal greetings
</P>
<P>
   Uncoated felt paper and paperboard in rolls or sheets
</P>
<P>
   Some lithographs on paper or paperboard
</P>
<P>
   Source: Office of the U.S. Trade Representative.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
