<SLUG> BC-SF-PUBLISHER-APPOINT-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WHITE SUCCEEDS GUITTAR AS PUBLISHER OF SAN FRANCISCO EXAMINER 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 c.1999 Hearst Newspapers  
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Timothy O. White, vice president and publisher of the
Albany Times Union, has been named publisher and editor of the San
Francisco Examiner, succeeding Lee J. Guittar, who is retiring
after a 31-year newspaper career.
</P>
<P>
   The appointment, effective immediately, was announced Friday by
George B. Irish, president of Hearst Newspapers and vice president
of The Hearst Corporation. Both the Examiner and the Times Union
are Hearst newspapers.
</P>
<P>
   ``Tim White has done a superb job in providing leadership to the
Albany Times Union over the last nine years, and we look forward to
his applying those talents to his new assignment in San
Francisco,'' Irish said.
</P>
<P>
   White, 56, has been publisher of the Times Union since 1990.
Previously, he was publisher of the Ann Arbor (Mich.) News. He
began his career as corporate marketing director for the Booth
Newspapers.
</P>
<P>
   He is a member of the Newspaper Association of America and has
served as chairman of the New York Newspaper Publishers
Association. He is active in civic affairs and is past chairman of
the Center for Economic Growth in New York's capital region. He
holds a B.A. from Yale University and an M.B.A. from the University
of Chicago.
</P>
<P>
   Guittar, 67, who also served as a vice president of The Hearst
Corporation, ``is concluding a remarkable career which included
leadership roles in Miami, Detroit, Dallas and Denver, as well as
the launch of USA Today,'' Irish noted. ``We are most grateful for
the leadership that Lee brought to San Francisco and to Hearst
Newspapers in his corporate role.''
</P>
<P>
   Hearst Newspapers is an operating group of The Hearst
Corporation.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
