<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-08 14:40 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A4919 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FEATURE-BUDGET-BOS &LR;      01-08 0795
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FEATURE-BUDGET-BOS </SLUG>
  
 For Immediate Release  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following FEATURE stories for
use by NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; IMPEACH (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-LEGAL (Washington) -- House Republicans, who argued
during the impeachment process that it wasn't necessary to call
witnesses to present a strong case against President Clinton, now
say it's essential. By Adam Pertman. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   LA-MURDERS (Sulphur, La.) _ At first, there appeared to be an
