   CLINTON-IMPEACHMENT (Washington) _ The Senate agrees on
procedures for President Clinton's impeachment trial but delays a
decision on calling witnesses. House prosecutors will begin their
case for Clinton's removal next week. By STEWART M. POWELL and JUDY
HOLLAND.
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH-POLITICS (Washington) _ Sidebar on how the impeachment
proceedings will impact both parties. By BENNETT ROTH.
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACHMENT-PENS (Washington) _ Political memorabilia mavens,
take note: The pens used by senators to sign an ``oath book'' at
the opening of President Clinton's impeachment trial Thursday may
ultimately fetch $100 on the collectors' market. The black and
silver Parker Vector pens, standard issue in the U.S. Senate,
retail for about $10. By ERIC ROSENBERG.
</P>
<P>
   US-IRAQ (Washington) _ The Pentagon has doubled its damage
estimate from last month's airstrikes on Iraq, saying the attack
set back Saddam Hussein's weapons program two years and killed 600
to 2,000 Republican Guard members, including key leaders. By STEVE
LASH.
</P>
