<HEADER>
A5138 &Cx1f; taf-z
u l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-STYLE-BUDGET-NYT &LR;      01-08 0489
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-STYLE-BUDGET-NYT </SLUG>
  
 Attn: Style and Leisure Editors:  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service plans the following articles
from the Style section for use Sunday, Jan. 10, and thereafter. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIAN-ICEDANCER (New York) _ What do you get the teen-age girl
who has everything? A horse? A Miata? How about a real live Russian
ice-dance partner? Two years ago, when Ariel Williams, then a 10th
grader at the Dalton School in Manhattan, began to show promise in
ice dancing, her mother, Marian Williams, scouted for a full-time
partner for her. The search led to Dmitri Boundoukin, a
Russian-born skater who was soap-opera handsome. By Marcia
Biederman. Photo. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   NEW-AGE-COSMETICS (New York) _ If you are looking for
enlightenment in all the wrong places, how nice that cosmetics
companies are suddenly so eager to help. Because today, in
``Darwin's empty heaven,'' as the writer Chip Brown puts it in his
new book, ``Afterwards, You're a Genius: Faith, Medicine and the
Metaphysics of Healing'' (Riverhead Books), feeling good is the new
religion. And cosmetics companies are the newest of the new
prophets, turning the old notion of hope in a jar on its head. By
Penelope Green. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   REDMAN-SHOPPING (New York) _ On a shopping trip with Joshua
Redman, the jazz musician. By Eric Asimov. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   WANNABE-CELEBRITIES (New York) _ Forget Michael Jordan, Cindy
Crawford, Bill Cosby and the other superstars and supermodels. Here
comes a phalanx of the prefamous: gonnabes, wannabes and whozzats
peddling products in commercials, ads and billboards as if they
were instantly recognizable. Some are totally unknown. Others are
second- or third-tier stars. By Stuart Elliott. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   TRUMP-PAGEANT (New York) _ On Thursday, the temperature had
dropped to a sub-freezing chill, but at Life, the nightclub on
Bleecker Street, things were heating up. Donald J. Trump, the real
estate developer, was expected at any moment for a promotional
party for the Miss U.S.A. Pageant, which will be broadcast live
next month on CBS. By Bob Morris. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   GARDEN-COLUMN (Undated) _ The tree tomato is one of those
beguiling novelties that the nursery trade is so fond of. It's not
a tomato at all, although it's a member of the same family, the
Solanaceae. It is a tropical shrub with the botanical name
Cyphomandra betacea. Its fruit _ which is usually yellowish-orange
rather than red _ is edible, but it doesn't taste like a tomato. By
Cass Peterson.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   QUESTIONS OR RERUNS: (888) 346-9867
</P>
<P>
   Weekdays, Arceanious Felton (e-mail, arfelton(at)nytimes.com).
</P>
