<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients)  
. 
The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``e'' entertainment news file. For questions, contact Jimmy
Johnson at the Daily News, (818) 713-3695. 
. 
DIGITAL-TECH (Los Angeles) _ A year ago, Apple Computers seemed
headed to the electronic graveyard, its spark shorting out on
staggering market share, gun-shy developers and wavering
supporters. But as the old song nearly says, what a difference a
year makes. At this week's MacWorld Expo in San Francisco, interim
CEO Steve Jobs unveiled a bunch of new machines and initiatives
that capitalize on the remarkable momentum the company built with
its original iMac. By David Bloom. 
. 
PURGATORY-TV (Los Angeles) _ Refuge is a quiet town, tucked away in
a verdant valley. No newspapers here, though, nor a telegraph.
Drinks are free at the saloon, and the doctor sure is nice about
patching up folks for nothing. The sheriff doesn't even pack a gun,
though he does look familiar. It is into this odd little burg that
Blackjack (Eric Roberts) and his gang of about 20 bad guys ride
after a particularly bloody bank heist. By David Bloom. 
. 
The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``l'' lifestyle news file. For questions, contact Jimmy Johnson
at the Daily News, (818) 713-3695. 
. 
PLAY-GAMES (Los Angeles) _ Despite manufacturers' efforts to
promote ``get together games,'' sales last year were only about
one-quarter of the nearly $4 billion in sales of computer and video
games, according to the NPD Research Group marketing firm. But
makers of several new family-oriented games, including an Encino
teen, is gambling on that changing. By Carol Bidwell. 
. 
BOARD-GAMES (Los Angeles) _ Toy stores are selling all kinds of
interactive games _ and we're not talking about the kind you plug
into a computer. Board games _ old and new _ provide all kinds of
``get together'' opportunities for families and friends. By Carol
Bidwell. 
. 

<TEXT>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-08-99 1732EST &QL; 
