   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Saturday, Jan. 9. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
KEATING (Undated) - U.S. District Court judge in Los Angeles has
set a Monday hearing at which prosecutors are expected to announce
their intention to retry former savings and loan chief Charles H
Keating Jr on charges that he looted Lincoln Savings. By JERRY
KAMMER. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
BIKERS (Phoenix) - Harley motorcycle dealers and Sheriff Joe Arpaio
announce a weeklong motorcycle rally set for March, running in
conjunction with racing events at Phoenix International Raceway.
This could mean 100,000 bikers coming to town on roaring Harleys.
By BOB GOLFEN. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
QUAYLE (Phoenix) - Former Vice President Dan Quayle likely will
form a presidential exploratory campaign committee next month,
putting him in competition with another Arizonan, Sen. John McCain,
in the first test of the GOP presidential primary: A candidate must
raise up to $60,000 a day this year to be considered a serious
contender in 2000. By MICHAEL MURPHY. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
AUTO-REVIEW (Phoenix) - The most remarkable thing about the Honda
Civic GX, powered by compressed natural gas (CNG), is that it's so
unremarkable.
</P>
<P>
   The driveability of the natural-gas Civic feels nearly identical
to a run-of-the-mill, gasoline-powered Civic. Maybe a bit light on
torque at low engine speeds, but otherwise a normal Honda
experience.
</P>
<P>
   The big exception is that the CNG Civic produces 20 percent less
greenhouse gas emissions than an equivalent gasoline vehicle, and
emits nearly zero hydrocarbons. The flip side is that cruising
range is limited to about 200 miles per tank of CNG, and CNG can be
hard to come by. By BOB GOLFEN. Story will move in the ``L''
category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
