Friday that ``Euroland'' was not the proper word, in France at
least, for the group of 11 countries that have introduced the euro
as their new common currency this year. Call it ``the euro zone,''
the Academy decreed: after all, was the United States
``Dollarland?'' Was Britain ``Sterlingland?'' By Craig R. Whitney.
</P>
