expected in December and the unemployment rate fell, tying a
28-year low. Payrolls increased by 378,000 jobs last month, well
above analysts' forecasts. The unemployment rate declined to 4.3
percent in December from 4.4 percent in November. By Sylvia Nasar.
</P>
