<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    '98 Dogs draw record crowds at Sanford
 &HT;    By Plott Brice
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATHENS _ The Georgia Bulldogs set a single-season attendance
record at Sanford Stadium in the fall, good enough for the
fifth-best average attendance in the nation.
</P>
<P>
   Figures released by the NCAA show Georgia with an average
attendance of 85,618 in the 86,117 capacity stadium. The old mark
was 83,948 in 1995 when Alabama , Florida and Auburn played in
Athens.
</P>
<P>
   It was the 14th time in the last 18 years that Georgia finished
among the top six teams in the nation in average home attendance.
</P>
<P>
   The nation's top 10: Michigan, 110,965; Tennessee, 106,914; Penn
State, 96,532; Ohio State, 93,502; Georgia, 85,618; Florida,
85,299; Alabama, 82,670; Auburn, 81,110; Florida State, 80,490; and
LSU, 80,290.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
