<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following for
clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of Saturday, Jan.
9, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please call Larry
Johnson at (206) 448-8035.
</P>
<P>
   GORTON-ROLE (Washington) _ Sen. Slade Gorton would have spent
Friday celebrating anyway _ it was his 71st birthday. But Gorton,
R-Wash., was also celebrating what he called ``one of the most
rewarding experiences I've had in the Senate,'' a central role in
developing the bipartisan plan for proceeding with the impeachment
trial of President Clinton.
