<DOCNO> NYT19990108.0431 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-08 21:28 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5601 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-FALCONS-HISTORY09     01-08 0632
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-FALCONS-HISTORY09-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Experience is on side of ... well, you know
 &HT;    By Karen Rosen
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ For the San Francisco 49ers, the voice of experience
is Steve Young or Jerry Rice, who have won three Super Bowl rings
each while appearing in a combined 43 playoff games.
</P>
<P>
   To the Falcons, whose players have participated in a total of 76
postseason games and only nine with Atlanta, it is cornerback Ray
Buchanan saying, ``We're not thinking about our past. It's all
about the present once you get out there on the football field.''
</P>
<P>
   The Falcons are aware that San Francisco's playoff span is about
as long as the Golden Gate Bridge, and they don't care.
</P>
<P>
   ``It just shows that we want it more,'' cornerback Michael
Booker said. ``They've been there; it's old hat to them. We want to
make a statement to the world and the NFL that we are a contending
team and that we are the team of the new millennium. This is our
start right here.''
</P>
<P>
   Linebacker Cornelius Bennett wants to make sure it's not their
finish.
</P>
<P>
   ``What I'm trying to communicate to these guys is that what we
did two weeks ago against Miami is not good enough now,'' said
Bennett, who played in 17 playoff games with Buffalo.
</P>
<P>
   ``If we say, `They've got Super Bowl rings,' we're going to be
defeated before we take the field. What I have to tell our players
is that (the 49ers), by their experience, know they have to pick up
their level of play during the playoffs, and we're going to have to
match it or be better than they are (today) on.''
</P>
<P>
   Among the 53 Falcons, 20 have playoff experience, but only 12
have appeared in more than one game. Among the 49ers, the
winningest team of the 1980s and '90s, 45 have been in the
playoffs, 34 in more than one game.
</P>
<P>
   Free safety Eugene Robinson (Green Bay) and wide receiver Tony
Martin (Miami and San Diego) each have appeared in eight playoff
games. Cornerback Randy Fuller played seven games with Pittsburgh.
</P>
<P>
   ``Of course, (playoff experience) makes a difference,'' Fuller
said. ``An organization that's used to winning, they go into all
games expecting to win.''
</P>
<P>
   Yet at 14-2, these Falcons have become used to winning, too.
</P>
<P>
   Fuller offered this advice to his teammates: ``Make sure you
study, and you're focused and ready to play.''
</P>
<P>
   He also has tantalized them with tales of participating in a
Super Bowl. He played in Super Bowl XXX with the Steelers.
</P>
<P>
   ``When you get to the Super Bowl, it's like you're a superstar,
regardless of how much you played or what position you are,'' he
said. ``I just want everybody to feel that excitement that I felt
once.''
</P>
<P>
   Quarterback Chris Chandler, who has never played in the
postseason, said he ``would hope'' playoff experience isn't a
factor.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a football game, and definitely the intensity level is
going to pick up,'' Chandler said. ``But there's no real secret in
a playoff game. It's just (that) you've gotta play really, really
good football.''
</P>
<P>
   Running back Jamal Anderson said he thinks the 49ers' additional
playoff experience will be a factor only ``if you allow it to be. I
know nobody on this team is going `Wow, gosh, they've been to a lot
of Super Bowls. Woooo.' Who cares?''
</P>
<P>
   He added, ``We're trying to gain playoff experience.''
</P>
<P>
   Coach Dan Reeves, who will be participating in his 46th playoff
game, said the Falcons also can learn from players whose seasons
have ended in December.
</P>
<P>
   ``Jessie Tuggle has been involved in some playoffs but has gone
through the hard times,'' Reeves said, ``and Terance Mathis _ it
has been invaluable to have those kind of guys, because you
understand the other side of it and how special this is.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
