<SLUG> BC-AIRTOUCH-MCI-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MCI WON'T MAKE BID FOR AIRTOUCH
</HEADLINE>
 (bl) 
c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Speculation over whether MCI Worldcom Inc. would join the
bidding for Airtouch Communications Inc. appeared all for naught
Friday. MCI Worldcom said in a press release that after reviewing
the possibility of acquiring Airtouch, it had ``determined not to
pursue a bid for the company at this time.''
</P>
<P>
   The statement came after news reports earlier in the day that
MCI Worldcom had made a verbal offer to buy Airtouch in a stock
swap.
</P>
<P>
   Airtouch, the nation's leading wireless phone company, has been
in merger talks with Bell Atlantic, the nation's largest local
phone concern, which wants to buy the company in a stock deal
valued at about $45 billion. Last weekend Vodafone Group PLC, a
British wireless carrier, proposed buying Airtouch for cash and
securities worth about $54 billion.
</P>
<P>
   While Airtouch is clearly the company in play, some merger
professionals said Friday that Vodafone might find itself an
attractive target, particularly for European telecommunications
concerns that want to expand.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
