<HEADLINE>
MADDEN SELECTS PLUMMER 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By LEE SHAPPELL  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEMPE, ARIZ. - Second-year quarterback  &UR; Jake Plummer will be
named to this season's All-Madden Team by Fox TV analyst  &UR; John
Madden, it was learned Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Madden annually bestows the honor upon players who personify a
blue-collar work-ethic and grit.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's fitting,'' said  &UR; Aeneas Williams, the Cardinals five-time
Pro Bowl cornerback who works against Plummer in practice. ``He
made plays the old-fashioned way, by moving around.''
</P>
<P>
   Right tackle  &UR; James Dexter, who also does the type of grunt work
that Madden loves, upon hearing the news about Plummer, blurted
out, ``Awesome!''
</P>
<P>
   Plummer, as he does an on-rushing defensive end, took it in
stride.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's cool,'' Plummer said. ``It's a fun kind of team. I think
it's just because I've been kind of scrappy, and not afraid to get
dirty.'' &QL; 
Looking good &QL; 
Cardinals Coach  &UR; Vince Tobin was upbeat Friday after what he called
three great days of practice. The Cardinals got to Minnesota as
healthy as they've been in a month.
</P>
<P>
   ``As far as people who are active, we certainly are,'' he said.
``Everybody practiced, and I think that's the first time that's
happened on Friday in probably the last three or four weeks.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think the last two or three practices have been great. The
players' attitude, their attention to detail, I couldn't have asked
for more. We've got 48 hours before we play. We've got to retain
that and build our emotions so that Sunday we're ready to go. As
far as what we accomplished this week in practice, I think we
accomplished everything we can.''
</P>
<P>
   Getting the focus ahead instead of behind is a major
accomplishment in itself, according to Tobin.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think each time that you have success it builds your
confidence and builds your ability to think that you can do even
more good things,'' Tobin said. ``That's something that until
you've experienced it I don't think anybody realizes how good you
can be.'' &QL; 
Briefly &QL; 
On Friday, Tobin declared cornerback  &UR; Ty Howard, offensive lineman
 &UR; Jerome &UR; Daniels, wide receiver  &UR; Ronnie Anderson and defensive end
 &UR; Jomo Cousins inactive.
</P>
<P>
   For anyone who gets up early and has a last-minute craving to
take in the game in person, there are limited spots still available
on a charter plane available through Baker Travel. The package is
priced at $859, including air fare, ground transportation, game
ticket, and one night at the team hotel. Reservations may be made
24 hours a day at 998-8922. &QL; 
Republic reporters Steve Schoenfeld, Lee Shappell and Tim Tyers
contributed to this report. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
