<HEADLINE>
TWO ARRESTED IN 1997 SLAYING OF SOLDIER AT COLORADO FORT 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By RICHARD ESPINOZA  
 c. 1999 Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   OVERLAND PARK, Kan. _ Two soldiers have been arrested in the
1997 stabbing death of an Overland Park man who was killed while
stationed at Fort Carson, Colo.
</P>
<P>
   Military police arrested the men Wednesday night after
authorities received an anonymous call about the death of
20-year-old Pfc. Jason M. Chafin.
</P>
<P>
   A 25-year-old St. Louis man was being held in Germany, where he
is stationed with the Army, and a 24-year-old Montgomery, Ala., man
was in custody at Fort Carson. Both had been stationed with Chafin
at Fort Carson when he disappeared Aug. 29, 1997. Rabbit hunters
found his body in a ravine about 10 miles from the fort on Dec. 26
of that year.
</P>
<P>
   No one has been charged, and investigators would not talk about
a motive in Chafin's death.
</P>
<P>
   Chafin had been scheduled to start duty in Kuwait when he
disappeared, but he had said he was afraid he would be killed, his
father said. Michael Chafin didn't know whether his son was talking
about a threat or about dying in military action.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
