<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-CARDS-EXHIBITION-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PRESEASON GAME IN MEXICO LIKELY  
 CARDS MAY ALSO PLAY ON MONDAY NIGHT 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By STEVE SCHOENFELD  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEMPE, ARIZ. - The NFL is expected to inform the Cardinals by
the end of the month that they will meet the Pittsburgh Steelers in
an American Bowl preseason game next August in Monterrey, Mexico,
another indication of the team's newfound popularity.
</P>
<P>
   It will be the Cardinals' first international game since moving
to Arizona in 1988 and the franchise's first since playing in
London in 1983.
</P>
<P>
   Until this year, the Cardinals hadn't had a winning season since
1984 or been in the playoffs since 1982.
</P>
<P>
   In addition to playing an international game, the Cardinals are
likely next season to make their first appearance on Monday Night
Football since 1995.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think we'll see more of that,'' said Cardinals Vice
President Larry Wilson. ``That comes along with winning and having
an exciting team.
</P>
<P>
   ``All you have to do is look at the TV numbers generated the
last few weeks here and throughout the country when we've been on.
There is a lot of interest in this football team.''
</P>
<P>
   Channels 5 and 15 in Phoenix televised the Cardinals' games the
past two weeks and recorded the largest number of viewers in
station history.
</P>
<P>
   In fact, the Cardinals' first-round playoff victory over Dallas
drew a 35.7 rating and a 64 share on Channel 15, which also carried
the Fiesta Bowl. That national-championship game between Tennessee
and Florida State drew a 13.7 rating and 19 share.
</P>
<P>
   Dennis Lewin, the NFL's senior vice president-broadcasting and
network television, said the Cardinals will get strong
consideration for a Monday Night Football game next year.
</P>
<P>
   ``Nothing has been decided yet, and we won't make those
decisions until the spring, but they have an up-and-coming team and
an exciting young quarterback,'' Lewin said of Jake Plummer. ``The
whole country has taken note of what the Cardinals have done.''
</P>
<P>
   Wilson said the team was supposed to hear from the league a week
ago about the status of the international game.
</P>
<P>
   A league source said final details still are being worked out,
but that the game is expected to be played the second or third week
of the preseason.
</P>
<P>
   It will be the first NFL game played in Monterrey. However, the
San Diego Padres of the National League have played there in a
40,000-seat baseball stadium.
</P>
<P>
   Although the Cardinals are not well-known in Mexico, the
Steelers are the second-most popular NFL team there, according to a
poll by NFL Properties. The Dallas Cowboys are the most popular
team in Mexico and drew 106,424 fans for a preseason game against
New England last summer at Azteca Stadium in Mexico City.
</P>
<P>
   The 1999 preseason schedule hasn't been a completed, but a
source close to the Denver Broncos said they will play host to the
Cardinals in the opener next year. The Broncos were supposed to
play the St. Louis Rams, but the Rams have asked for a bye the
first week of the preseason. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
