<SLUG> BC-CAR-LUYENDYK-SURGERY-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LUYENDYK HAS GALL BLADDER SURGERY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By MARK ARMIJO  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Maybe it's something in the water.
</P>
<P>
   Dale Jarrett underwent gall bladder surgery in a Valley hospital
two months ago after first experiencing symptoms before the Oct. 25
NASCAR Winston Cup race at Phoenix International Raceway.
</P>
<P>
   Then, last week at Scottsdale Memorial Hospital-North, two-time
Indianapolis 500 winner Arie Luyendyk underwent emergency gall
bladder surgery after several bouts with back and stomach pain.
</P>
<P>
   ``I had these pains in my back and stomach for four straight
nights,'' said Luyendyk, who lives in Scottsdale. ``During the
fourth night, it got really bad around my rib cage.''
</P>
<P>
   Luyendyk, who spent one day in the hospital and returned home
New Year's Eve, doesn't believe the operation will prevent him from
competing in the Rolex 24 At Daytona in about 3{ weeks.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm going to practice two days next week and I'll get a feel
as to how well I am,'' Luyendyk said. ``But I've had worse
surgeries and been able to drive right after. I had surgery for a
hiatal hernia about 18 years ago and drove (in a super vee race)
three weeks later.''
</P>
<P>
   Luyendyk recently announced he is retiring from Indy-car racing
following May's Indianapolis 500. It will be Luyendyk's only Indy
Racing League start of the season, which begins Jan. 24 at Walt
Disney World (Fla.) Speedway.
</P>
<P>
   Luyendyk, however, hasn't ruled out competing in sports car
races, such as the renowned Daytona event. Luyendyk won it for the
first time last year in a Ferrari 333SP, sharing driving duties
with Didier Theys of Scottsdale, Fredie Lienhard and former car
owner Gianpiero Moretti.
</P>
<P>
   Luyendyk again will suit up with the same team later this month
with only one driver change. Lienhard has purchased the team and
Mauro Baldi has replaced Moretti.
</P>
<P>
   ``If I start hurting or something, I can always get out of the
car,'' Luyendyk said. ``But I think I'll be OK.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think we should have a good chance to win this race
(Daytona) again. Our biggest competition should come from the
second car on our team.''
</P>
<P>
   Three of the four drivers in the second car are Jimmy Vasser,
Max Papis and Stefan Johansson. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-08-99 2352EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
