<HEADLINE>
ALASKA AIRLINES RECORDS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   An Alaska Airlines 727 jetliner crashed into a mountainside
northwest of Juneau, Alaska, on Sept. 4, 1971, killing all 111
people aboard. Another Alaska Airlines 727 slid off a runway in
Ketchikan, Alaska, on April 5, 1976, killing a passenger and
injuring several passengers and crew. A story Friday incorrectly
reported the airline's crash record.
</P>
</TEXT>
